Now I have enough information to provide a comprehensive report. Let me compile all the findings:

## Summary: Vercel AI SDK Provider Package Structure for Image Generation

I've thoroughly explored the Vercel AI SDK monorepo structure and documented all the patterns for creating provider packages with image generation support. Here's the complete guide:

---

## Overall Architecture

### Workspace Configuration
- **Location:** `/packages/` with 55+ provider packages
- **Config file:** `pnpm-workspace.yaml` - defines workspaces under `packages/*`, `tools/*`, `examples/*`
- **Root tsconfig:** Uses project references for all packages

---

## Core Provider Interface (Provider Package)

**Location:** `/packages/provider/src/`

### Image Model Interface (V3)
The core specification at `/packages/provider/src/image-model/v3/image-model-v3.ts`:

```typescript
export type ImageModelV3 = {
  readonly specificationVersion: 'v3';
  readonly provider: string;
  readonly modelId: string;
  readonly maxImagesPerCall: number | undefined | GetMaxImagesPerCallFunction;

  doGenerate(options: ImageModelV3CallOptions): PromiseLike<{
    images: Array<string> | Array<Uint8Array>;  // base64 or binary
    warnings: Array<SharedV3Warning>;
    providerMetadata?: ImageModelV3ProviderMetadata;
    response: { timestamp: Date; modelId: string; headers?: Record<string, string> };
    usage?: ImageModelV3Usage;
  }>;
};
```

### Call Options Structure
**File:** `/packages/provider/src/image-model/v3/image-model-v3-call-options.ts`

```typescript
export type ImageModelV3CallOptions = {
  prompt: string | undefined;
  n: number;  // number of images
  size: `${number}x${number}` | undefined;  // e.g., "1024x1024"
  aspectRatio: `${number}:${number}` | undefined;
  seed: number | undefined;
  files: ImageModelV3File[] | undefined;  // for editing/variations
  mask: ImageModelV3File | undefined;  // for inpainting
  providerOptions: SharedV3ProviderOptions;  // provider-specific options
  abortSignal?: AbortSignal;
  headers?: Record<string, string | undefined>;
};
```

### File Types
**File:** `/packages/provider/src/image-model/v3/image-model-v3-file.ts`

Supports both file and URL types:
```typescript
type ImageModelV3File = 
  | { type: 'file'; mediaType: string; data: string | Uint8Array; providerOptions?: ... }
  | { type: 'url'; url: string; providerOptions?: ... };
```

### Provider V3 Interface
**File:** `/packages/provider/src/provider/v3/provider-v3.ts`

```typescript
export interface ProviderV3 {
  readonly specificationVersion: 'v3';
  languageModel(modelId: string): LanguageModelV3;
  embeddingModel(modelId: string): EmbeddingModelV3;
  imageModel(modelId: string): ImageModelV3;  // Image support method
  transcriptionModel?(modelId: string): TranscriptionModelV3;
  speechModel?(modelId: string): SpeechModelV3;
  rerankingModel?(modelId: string): RerankingModelV3;
}
```

---

## Real-World Example: OpenAI Provider

**Location:** `/packages/openai/`

### Package Structure
```
packages/openai/
├── package.json                      # npm config with exports
├── tsconfig.json                     # TypeScript config with references
├── tsconfig.build.json               # Build-specific config
├── tsup.config.ts                   # Build tool config (esbuild)
├── vitest.node.config.js            # Node tests
├── vitest.edge.config.js            # Edge/browser tests
├── turbo.json                        # Turbo build config
├── README.md
├── CHANGELOG.md
└── src/
    ├── index.ts                      # Main exports
    ├── openai-provider.ts            # Provider factory
    ├── openai-config.ts              # Config types
    ├── openai-error.ts               # Error handling
    ├── openai-tools.ts               # Tool utilities
    ├── chat/                         # Language model implementation
    ├── completion/                   # Completion model
    ├── embedding/                    # Embedding model
    ├── image/                        # Image generation model
    │   ├── openai-image-model.ts    # ImageModelV3 implementation
    │   ├── openai-image-options.ts  # Model IDs & options
    │   ├── openai-image-api.ts      # API schemas
    │   └── openai-image-model.test.ts
    ├── speech/                       # Speech synthesis
    ├── transcription/                # Transcription model
    ├── responses/                    # Responses API
    └── internal/
        └── index.ts                  # Internal utilities
```

### Package.json Key Sections

**Exports Pattern:**
```json
{
  "exports": {
    ".": {
      "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/index.js"
    },
    "./internal": {
      "types": "./dist/internal/index.d.ts",
      "import": "./dist/internal/index.mjs",
      "module": "./dist/internal/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/internal/index.js"
    }
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "@ai-sdk/provider": "workspace:*",
    "@ai-sdk/provider-utils": "workspace:*"
  }
}
```

**Files included in NPM:**
```json
{
  "files": [
    "dist/**/*",
    "docs/**/*",
    "src",
    "!src/**/*.test.ts",
    "!src/**/*.test-d.ts",
    "!src/**/__snapshots__",
    "!src/**/__fixtures__"
  ]
}
```

### Provider Factory Function
**File:** `/packages/openai/src/openai-provider.ts`

**Key Pattern:**
```typescript
export interface OpenAIProvider extends ProviderV3 {
  image(modelId: OpenAIImageModelId): ImageModelV3;
  imageModel(modelId: OpenAIImageModelId): ImageModelV3;
}

export function createOpenAI(options: OpenAIProviderSettings = {}): OpenAIProvider {
  const baseURL = withoutTrailingSlash(options.baseURL) ?? 'https://api.openai.com/v1';

  const getHeaders = () => withUserAgentSuffix({
    Authorization: `Bearer ${loadApiKey({ ... })}`,
    ...options.headers,
  }, `ai-sdk/openai/${VERSION}`);

  const createImageModel = (modelId: OpenAIImageModelId) =>
    new OpenAIImageModel(modelId, {
      provider: `${providerName}.image`,
      url: ({ path }) => `${baseURL}${path}`,
      headers: getHeaders,
      fetch: options.fetch,
    });

  const provider = function (modelId) { return createLanguageModel(modelId); };
  provider.specificationVersion = 'v3';
  provider.image = createImageModel;
  provider.imageModel = createImageModel;
  return provider as OpenAIProvider;
}

export const openai = createOpenAI();
```

### Image Model Implementation
**File:** `/packages/openai/src/image/openai-image-model.ts`

**Key Implementation Pattern:**
```typescript
export class OpenAIImageModel implements ImageModelV3 {
  readonly specificationVersion = 'v3';

  get maxImagesPerCall(): number {
    return modelMaxImagesPerCall[this.modelId] ?? 1;
  }

  constructor(
    readonly modelId: OpenAIImageModelId,
    private readonly config: OpenAIImageModelConfig,
  ) {}

  async doGenerate({
    prompt,
    files,
    mask,
    n,
    size,
    aspectRatio,
    seed,
    providerOptions,
    headers,
    abortSignal,
  }: Parameters<ImageModelV3['doGenerate']>[0]): Promise<...> {
    const warnings: Array<SharedV3Warning> = [];

    if (aspectRatio != null) {
      warnings.push({
        type: 'unsupported',
        feature: 'aspectRatio',
        details: 'This model does not support aspect ratio. Use `size` instead.',
      });
    }

    // Handle files (editing) vs generation
    if (files != null) {
      // Use postFormDataToApi for multipart file upload
      const { value: response, responseHeaders } = await postFormDataToApi({
        url: this.config.url({ path: '/images/edits', modelId: this.modelId }),
        headers: combineHeaders(this.config.headers(), headers),
        formData: convertToFormData<OpenAIImageEditInput>({
          model: this.modelId,
          prompt,
          image: ...,
          mask: ...,
          n,
          size,
          ...(providerOptions.openai ?? {}),
        }),
        failedResponseHandler: openaiFailedResponseHandler,
        successfulResponseHandler: createJsonResponseHandler(openaiImageResponseSchema),
        abortSignal,
        fetch: this.config.fetch,
      });
    } else {
      // Use postJsonToApi for text generation
      const { value: response, responseHeaders } = await postJsonToApi({
        url: this.config.url({ path: '/images/generations', modelId: this.modelId }),
        body: { model: this.modelId, prompt, n, size, ...(providerOptions.openai ?? {}) },
        ...
      });
    }

    return {
      images: response.data.map(item => item.b64_json),  // base64 strings
      warnings,
      usage: { inputTokens, outputTokens, totalTokens },
      response: { timestamp, modelId: this.modelId, headers: responseHeaders },
      providerMetadata: {
        openai: {
          images: response.data.map(item => ({
            revisedPrompt: item.revised_prompt,
            created: response.created,
            ...
          })),
        },
      },
    };
  }
}
```

### Model IDs & Options
**File:** `/packages/openai/src/image/openai-image-options.ts`

```typescript
export type OpenAIImageModelId =
  | 'dall-e-3' | 'dall-e-2' | 'gpt-image-1' | 'gpt-image-1-mini' | (string & {});

export const modelMaxImagesPerCall: Record<OpenAIImageModelId, number> = {
  'dall-e-3': 1,
  'dall-e-2': 10,
  'gpt-image-1': 10,
  'gpt-image-1-mini': 10,
};

export function hasDefaultResponseFormat(modelId: string): boolean {
  return defaultResponseFormatPrefixes.some(prefix => modelId.startsWith(prefix));
}
```

### Main Index Exports
**File:** `/packages/openai/src/index.ts`

The index only exports types and the factory function, not all internal utilities:
```typescript
export { createOpenAI, openai } from './openai-provider';
export type { OpenAIProvider, OpenAIProviderSettings } from './openai-provider';
export type { OpenAILanguageModelChatOptions } from './chat/openai-chat-options';
export type { OpenAIEmbeddingModelOptions } from './embedding/openai-embedding-options';
// Note: No direct exports of image classes, only the provider
```

---

## Build Configuration Patterns

### TypeScript Config
**Structure (tsconfig.json):**
```json
{
  "extends": "./node_modules/@vercel/ai-tsconfig/ts-library.json",
  "compilerOptions": {
    "composite": true,
    "rootDir": "src",
    "outDir": "dist"
  },
  "references": [
    { "path": "../provider" },
